  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6952.15 sitting just above the massive 6950 gamma wall (20.7B), dealers are in active selling mode to hedge their long gamma positions, creating immediate resistance. The PIN regime with 136B in total GEX suggests strong mean-reverting forces, with dealers likely to fade this 0.9% 5-minute rally and push price back toward the 6900-6950 range. Key levels to watch: 6950 as immediate resistance where selling intensifies, 6900 as the next major support wall, and 6848 GEX flip as the critical break point where dealer behavior reverses.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect selling pressure and pullback from current levels with strong support around 6900-6920.",
